hopobject.body: Accountant supermarket manager acelrx pharma inc In 1971, six years before Ferguson committed his first murder, a court-appointed doctor diagnosed Ferguson as paranoid schizophrenic, saying he had a "severely damaged ability to distinguish right from wrong." In the mid-80s, a decade after Ferguson's crimes, Florida's state prison system described him as incompetent to stand before a court, saying he did not know what a judge was and did not understand a lawyer's function. And in 2004, Ferguson's schizophrenia was deemed "incurable."
